## Project-Invariant Directories

These directories belong to the reusable project framework. Do not move or rename them because the host OS, IDE, compiler, debugger, or AI Agent changes.

| Path | Role | Changes when | Exists |
|------|------|--------------|--------|
| `App` | project application layer | business/application behavior changes | yes |
| `Service` | project service abstraction layer | feature-level hardware services or orchestration change | yes |
| `Driver` | project driver API layer | board/MCU peripherals change, while preserving public layer contracts | yes |
| `Test` | project firmware test layer | behavior or driver/service test coverage changes | yes |
| `docs` | project knowledge base and reference notes | requirements, architecture, hardware facts, or workflow rules change | yes |
| `.context` | AI handoff fact source | engineering, hardware, version, or runtime facts change | yes |
| `.workflow` | project configuration source for tools and layout | project name, board, MCU, toolchain, output paths, serial, flash, or layout config changes | yes |
| `.agents` | agent-neutral AI workflow assets and canonical Skills | AI workflow entrypoints, Skills, or compatibility mirrors change | yes |
| `tools` | deterministic automation entry points | workflow actions or adapters change | yes |
| `reports` | current evidence snapshots for automation reports | build, flash, review, check, or verify evidence is refreshed | yes |

